const TEXTBOOK_SECTIONS = [{"name": "00-intro", "content": "# English Core Verbs & Prepositions\n\n## 이 책의 목표\n\n영어에서 가장 많이 쓰이는 동사 11개와 전치사 45개의 **감각**을 잡는다.\n한국어 뜻을 외우는 게 아니라, 네이티브가 이 단어를 쓸 때 머릿속에 떠오르는 이미지를 체득한다.\n\n## 이렇게 읽어라\n\n1. 한국어 뜻을 먼저 떠올리지 마라\n2. 핵심 감각 한 문장을 먼저 느껴라\n3. 예문을 소리 내서 읽어라\n4. 연습문제를 반드시 풀어라\n\n## 구성\n\n- **Part 1**: 핵심 동사 12개 — 이것만 알면 영어의 70%가 된다\n- **Part 2**: 전치사·부사 44개 — 동사에 방향과 뉘앙스를 입힌다"}, {"name": "01-get", "content": "# get\n\n> **핵심 감각: 변화** — A가 아닌 상태에서 A인 상태로 넘어가는 순간\n\n## 핵심 감각\n\nget의 모든 뜻은 **\"변화\"** 하나로 통한다. 무언가가 없던 데서 생기거나, 한 상태에서 다른 상태로 넘어가는 것. 뭐가 변하느냐에 따라 한국어 해석만 달라질 뿐이다.\n\n## 감각 갈래\n\n### 상태가 변하면 → ~해지다 ★★★★★\n가장 직관적인 변화. 밝음→어두움, 기운참→피곤함.\n- It's getting dark outside.\n- I got tired after the meeting.\n- She got angry at me.\n\n### 소유가 변하면 → 얻다 / 받다 ★★★★★\n없던 것이 내 손에 들어오는 변화. buy, receive, earn 전부 get으로 대체 가능.\n- I got a new phone yesterday.\n- Did you get my message?\n- She got a promotion last month.\n\n### 위치가 변하면 → 도착하다 ★★★★\n여기가 아닌 곳에서 여기로, 또는 여기서 거기로. arrive보다 훨씬 자주 씀.\n- What time did you get home?\n- How do I get to the station?\n\n### 인식이 변하면 → 이해하다 ★★★\n모르는 상태에서 아는 상태로. understand보다 캐주얼.\n- I don't get it. What do you mean?\n- Oh, I get it now!\n\n### 남의 상태를 변하게 하면 → 시키다 ★★★\n변화의 방향을 남에게 향하게 하는 것.\n- I got him to fix the computer.\n- Can you get the kids to be quiet?\n\n## 필수 패턴\n| 패턴 | 감각 | 예문 |\n|------|------|------|\n| get + 형용사 | 상태 변화 | She got angry at me. |\n| get + to + 장소 | 위치 변화 | How do I get to the airport? |\n| get + 사람 + to do | 남의 상태 변화 | I got her to help me. |\n| get rid of | 존재→없음 변화 | I need to get rid of this old sofa. |\n| get along with | 관계 변화 | Do you get along with your neighbors? |\n| get over | 상태 변화 (극복) | She got over the breakup quickly. |\n| get up | 위치 변화 (눕→섬) | I get up at 7 every morning. |\n| get out of | 위치 변화 (안→밖) | I want to get out of this meeting. |\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I got cold. → (O) I got a cold. (감기에 걸렸다)\n- (X) I get understand. → (O) I get it. (get 뒤에 동사원형 직접 안 옴)\n- (X) I got to home. → (O) I got home. (home 앞에 to 안 씀)\n\n## 연습\n\n1. It's _____ cold. Let's go inside. (getting / get)\n2. What time did you _____ home last night? (get / arrive)\n3. I don't _____ why she's angry. (get / know)\n4. Can you _____ him to call me back? (get / make)\n5. She finally _____ over her fear of flying. (got / got to)\n\n**정답**: 1. getting  2. get  3. get  4. get  5. got"}, {"name": "02-take", "content": "# take\n\n> **핵심 감각: 취하다** — 손을 뻗어 내 쪽으로 가져가는 동작\n\n## 핵심 감각\n\ntake의 모든 뜻은 **\"취하다\"** 하나로 통한다. 물건이든, 시간이든, 경험이든 — 무언가를 잡아서 내 것으로 가져가는 것. 뭘 취하느냐에 따라 해석이 달라질 뿐이다.\n\n## 감각 갈래\n\n### 물건·사람을 취하면 → 가져가다 / 데려가다 ★★★★★\n가장 기본. 잡아서 이동시키는 감각.\n- Take your umbrella. It might rain.\n- I'll take you to the airport.\n\n### 시간·노력을 취하면 → ~이 걸리다 ★★★★★\n무언가가 나의 시간/에너지를 가져가는 것.\n- It takes 30 minutes to get there.\n- This project took a lot of effort.\n\n### 선택지를 취하면 → 고르다 / 받아들이다 ★★★★\n여러 개 중 하나를 집어 드는 것.\n- I'll take the blue one.\n- Do you take credit cards?\n\n### 몸 안으로 취하면 → 먹다 / 복용하다 ★★★\n음식·약을 내 몸 안으로 가져가는 것. eat/drink보다 넓은 표현.\n- Take this medicine twice a day.\n- Let's take a break and grab coffee.\n\n### 경험을 취하면 → 수강하다 / 치르다 ★★★\n시험, 수업 등을 가져가서 겪는 것.\n- I'm taking a class this semester.\n- She took the exam yesterday.\n\n## 필수 패턴\n| 패턴 | 감각 | 예문 |\n|------|------|------|\n| take + 시간 | 시간을 취함 | It takes an hour by bus. |\n| take off | 벗다 / 이륙 | Take off your shoes. / The plane took off. |\n| take on | 떠맡다 | She took on more responsibility. |\n| take over | 인수하다 | He took over the company. |\n| take out | 꺼내다 | Take out your textbook. |\n| take care of | 돌보다 | I'll take care of it. |\n| take up | 시작하다 (취미) | I took up yoga last month. |\n\n## 함정\n- (X) It takes 30 minutes for get there. → (O) It takes 30 minutes to get there.\n- (X) I take a bus to go work. → (O) I take a bus to work.\n- (X) I'll take rest. → (O) I'll take a rest. (관사 필요)\n\n## 연습\n\n1. It _____ about two hours to finish. (takes / gets)\n2. Can I _____ this seat? (take / sit)\n3. She _____ off her coat and sat down. (took / put)\n4. He decided to _____ on the new project. (take / make)\n5. I need to _____ care of my dog this weekend. (take / have)\n\n**정답**: 1. takes  2. take  3. took  4. take  5. take"}, {"name": "03-make", "content": "# make\n\n> **핵심 감각: 만들어내다** — 없던 결과를 발생시키는 힘\n\n## 핵심 감각\n\nmake의 모든 뜻은 **\"결과를 만들어내다\"** 하나로 통한다. 물건이든, 감정이든, 돈이든, 결정이든 — 뭔가 없던 것이 생겨나는 것. 어떤 결과를 만드느냐에 따라 해석이 달라질 뿐이다.\n\n## 감각 갈래\n\n### 물건이라는 결과를 만들면 → 만들다 / 생산하다 ★★★★★\n가장 직관적. 재료에서 결과물이 나오는 것.\n- She made dinner for the family.\n- This car is made in Germany.\n\n### 감정·상태라는 결과를 만들면 → ~하게 만들다 ★★★★★\n누군가에게 변화를 일으키는 것. 가장 많이 쓰는 용법.\n- You make me happy.\n- The noise made it hard to sleep.\n\n### 돈이라는 결과를 만들면 → 벌다 ★★★★\n수입이라는 결과를 만들어내는 것.\n- He makes $5,000 a month.\n- She made a fortune in real estate.\n\n### 결정이라는 결과를 만들면 → 결정하다 ★★★\n마음속에 결론을 만드는 것.\n- I made a decision to quit.\n- Let's make a plan for the weekend.\n\n### 성공이라는 결과를 만들면 → 해내다 / 도달하다 ★★★\n목표에 닿는 결과를 만드는 것.\n- We made it just in time.\n- She finally made it to the top.\n\n## 필수 패턴\n| 패턴 | 감각 | 예문 |\n|------|------|------|\n| make + 목적어 + 형용사 | 상태를 만듦 | The rain made the road slippery. |\n| make + 목적어 + 동사원형 | 행동을 만듦 | He made me wait for an hour. |\n| make up | 구성 / 화해 / 꾸미다 | Let's make up. We shouldn't fight. |\n| make out | 알아보다 / 이해하다 | I can't make out what he's saying. |\n| make sure | 확인하다 | Make sure you lock the door. |\n| make sense | 이치에 맞다 | That doesn't make sense. |\n| make a difference | 변화를 만들다 | Every small action makes a difference. |\n\n## 함정\n- (X) She made me to cry. → (O) She made me cry. (make + 목적어 + 동사원형, to 안 씀)\n- (X) I make a mistake yesterday. → (O) I made a mistake yesterday. (과거형)\n- (X) It's made by wood. → (O) It's made of wood. (재질이 보이면 of, 변형되면 from)\n\n## 연습\n\n1. This song always _____ me feel better. (makes / does)\n2. She _____ a big mistake at work. (made / did)\n3. The team is _____ up of 10 people. (made / taken)\n4. Does this _____ sense to you? (make / have)\n5. We _____ it to the airport with 5 minutes to spare. (made / got)\n\n**정답**: 1. makes  2. made  3. made  4. make  5. made"}, {"name": "04-have", "content": "# have\n\n> **핵심 감각: 내 영역에 있다** — 내 안에, 내 손에, 내 경험 안에 존재하는 것\n\n## 핵심 감각\n\nhave의 모든 뜻은 **\"내 영역에 존재한다\"** 하나로 통한다. 물건이 내 손에, 음식이 내 몸에, 경험이 내 기억에, 의무가 내 어깨에 — 뭐가 내 영역에 있느냐에 따라 해석이 달라질 뿐이다.\n\n## 감각 갈래\n\n### 물건이 내 영역에 → 소유하다 / 가지다 ★★★★★\n가장 기본. 내 영역 안에 존재하는 것.\n- I have two brothers.\n- Do you have any questions?\n\n### 음식이 내 영역(몸)에 → 먹다 / 마시다 ★★★★★\n몸 안으로 들어오는 것. eat/drink보다 부드러운 표현.\n- Let's have lunch together.\n- I'll have a coffee, please.\n\n### 경험이 내 영역에 → 경험하다 / 겪다 ★★★★\n시간·상황을 내 안에서 겪는 것.\n- We had a great time at the party.\n- I had trouble finding the place.\n\n### 서비스가 내 영역에 → 시키다 ★★★\n행위의 결과를 내 것으로 가지는 것.\n- I had my hair cut yesterday.\n- I'll have someone call you back.\n\n### 의무가 내 영역에 → 해야 한다 (have to) ★★★★★\n해야 할 일이 내 어깨 위에 있는 것.\n- I have to go now.\n- You don't have to worry about it.\n\n## 필수 패턴\n| 패턴 | 감각 | 예문 |\n|------|------|------|\n| have to + 동사 | 의무가 내 영역에 | I have to finish this today. |\n| have + 목적어 + p.p. | 결과를 내 영역에 | I had my car fixed. |\n| have + 목적어 + 동사원형 | 행위를 내 영역에 | I'll have him check it. |\n| have been to | 경험이 내 영역에 | Have you been to Paris? |\n| have something to do with | 관련이 내 영역에 | It has nothing to do with me. |\n| have no idea | 지식이 내 영역에 없음 | I have no idea what happened. |\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I have 25 years old. → (O) I'm 25 years old. (나이는 be 동사)\n- (X) I have a headache since morning. → (O) I've had a headache since morning. (since = 현재완료)\n- (X) I had cut my hair. → (O) I had my hair cut. (시키다 구문 어순)\n\n## 연습\n\n1. Let's _____ dinner at that new restaurant. (have / eat)\n2. I _____ to leave early tomorrow. (have / must)\n3. She _____ her nails done at the salon. (had / made)\n4. We _____ a wonderful time on vacation. (had / got)\n5. This _____ nothing to do with you. (has / is)\n\n**정답**: 1. have  2. have  3. had  4. had  5. has"}, {"name": "05-give", "content": "# give\n\n> **핵심 감각: 넘기다** — 내 영역에서 상대 쪽으로 이동시키는 것\n\n## 핵심 감각\n\ngive의 모든 뜻은 **\"넘기다\"** 하나로 통한다. have가 \"내 영역에 있다\"면, give는 정반대로 \"내 영역에서 나가게 하다\". 물건이든, 정보든, 영향이든, 저항이든 — 뭘 넘기느냐에 따라 해석이 달라질 뿐이다.\n\n## 감각 갈래\n\n### 물건을 넘기면 → 주다 / 건네다 ★★★★★\n가장 기본. 내 손에서 상대 손으로.\n- Give me a second.\n- She gave him a birthday present.\n\n### 정보·감정을 넘기면 → 전달하다 ★★★★★\n물건이 아닌 것도 넘길 수 있다.\n- Can you give me some advice?\n- He gave a great speech.\n\n### 영향을 넘기면 → 유발하다 / 발생시키다 ★★★★\n상대에게 결과를 넘기는 것.\n- Spicy food gives me a stomachache.\n- This app gives you full control.\n\n### 저항을 넘기면 → 양보하다 / 무너지다 ★★★\n버티던 것을 포기하고 내어주는 것.\n- The door gave way under the pressure.\n- Don't give in to fear.\n\n## 필수 패턴\n| 패턴 | 감각 | 예문 |\n|------|------|------|\n| give up | 포기를 넘김 | Don't give up on your dreams. |\n| give in | 저항을 넘김 | She finally gave in and said yes. |\n| give out | 밖으로 넘김 / 기능을 넘김 | They gave out free samples. |\n| give away | 완전히 넘김 | Don't give away the ending. |\n| give back | 되돌려 넘김 | Give me back my book. |\n| give off | 발산해서 넘김 | The flowers give off a nice smell. |\n\n## 함정\n- (X) She gave to me a book. → (O) She gave me a book. (give + 간접목적어 + 직접목적어)\n- (X) I'll give a try. → (O) I'll give it a try. (it 필요)\n- (X) He gave up to smoke. → (O) He gave up smoking. (give up + -ing)\n\n## 연습\n\n1. Can you _____ me a hand with this? (give / take)\n2. She _____ up trying to fix it. (gave / got)\n3. They _____ out flyers at the entrance. (gave / put)\n4. This medicine _____ me a headache. (gives / makes)\n5. Don't _____ away the surprise! (give / tell)\n\n**정답**: 1. give  2. gave  3. gave  4. gives  5. give"}, {"name": "06-go", "content": "# go\n\n> **핵심 감각: 떠남** — 지금 여기에서 멀어지는 것\n\n## 핵심 감각\n\ngo의 모든 뜻은 **\"떠남\"** 하나로 통한다. 장소를 떠나든, 원래 상태를 떠나든, 존재 자체를 떠나든 — 지금 있는 곳/상태에서 멀어지는 것. 뭘 떠나느냐에 따라 해석이 달라질 뿐이다.\n\n## 감각 갈래\n\n### 위치를 떠나면 → 이동하다 / 가다 ★★★★★\n가장 기본. 여기서 저기로. come과 반대 방향.\n- I'm going to the store.\n- She went to Paris last summer.\n\n### 시간이 떠나면 → 진행되다 / 흘러가다 ★★★★★\n일이 흘러가는 것.\n- How did the interview go?\n- Everything is going well.\n\n### 원래 상태를 떠나면 → ~해지다 (부정적 변화) ★★★★\n정상에서 벗어나는 변화. 주로 나쁜 방향.\n- The milk went bad.\n- He's going crazy with all this work.\n\n### 존재를 떠나면 → 사라지다 / 없어지다 ★★★\n떠나서 더 이상 없는 것.\n- My headache is gone.\n- Where did all the money go?\n\n### 현재를 떠나 미래로 → ~하려고 하다 (be going to) ★★★★★\n지금을 떠나 앞으로 향하는 것.\n- I'm going to study abroad.\n- It's going to rain.\n\n## 필수 패턴\n| 패턴 | 감각 | 예문 |\n|------|------|------|\n| go on | 멈춤을 떠남 (계속) | Go on. I'm listening. |\n| go out | 안을 떠남 | Let's go out for dinner. |\n| go off | 평상을 떠남 (작동) | The alarm went off at 6 a.m. |\n| go through | 통과하며 떠남 (겪다) | She's going through a tough time. |\n| go over | 위로 넘어감 (검토) | Let's go over the plan one more time. |\n| go for | ~을 향해 떠남 (선택) | I'll go for the cheaper option. |\n| go ahead | 앞으로 떠남 (진행) | Go ahead. I'll catch up. |\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I go to home. → (O) I go home. (home에 to 안 씀)\n- (X) I went to shopping. → (O) I went shopping. (go + -ing)\n- (X) Let's go to walk. → (O) Let's go for a walk.\n\n## 연습\n\n1. How did your presentation _____? (go / do)\n2. The fire alarm _____ off in the middle of the night. (went / got)\n3. I'm _____ to start a new job next week. (going / getting)\n4. She _____ through a lot last year. (went / took)\n5. _____ ahead and start without me. (Go / Get)\n\n**정답**: 1. go  2. went  3. going  4. went  5. Go"}, {"name": "07-come", "content": "# come\n\n> **핵심 감각: 다가옴** — 화자 쪽으로 가까워지는 것. go의 정반대.\n\n## 핵심 감각\n\ncome의 모든 뜻은 **\"다가옴\"** 하나로 통한다. go가 \"떠남\"이면 come은 \"다가옴\". 사람이든, 계절이든, 결과든, 출발점이든 — 뭐가 다가오느냐에 따라 해석이 달라질 뿐이다.\n\n## 감각 갈래\n\n### 사람·물건이 다가오면 → 오다 ★★★★★\n가장 기본. go가 떠남이면 come은 다가옴. 시점이 핵심.\n- Come here for a second.\n- She came to my house yesterday.\n\n### 존재가 다가오면 → 출현하다 / 나타나다 ★★★★\n없던 것이 세상에 모습을 드러내는 것.\n- Spring has come.\n- The answer came to me suddenly.\n\n### 결과가 다가오면 → 이르다 / 도달하다 ★★★★\n어떤 상태나 수치에 닿는 것.\n- The total comes to $50.\n- How did it come to this?\n\n### 출발점에서 다가왔으면 → 출신이다 / 비롯되다 ★★★\n어디서부터 여기까지 온 것.\n- Where do you come from?\n- This word comes from Latin.\n\n## 필수 패턴\n| 패턴 | 감각 | 예문 |\n|------|------|------|\n| come up | 위로 다가옴 (화제에 오름) | Something came up. I can't make it. |\n| come out | 밖으로 다가옴 (출시) | The new iPhone comes out next month. |\n| come across | 건너편에서 다가옴 (우연) | I came across an old photo. |\n| come along | 함께 다가옴 (진행) | The project is coming along nicely. |\n| come over | 넘어서 다가옴 (방문) | Come over to my place tonight. |\n| come up with | 떠올라 다가옴 (생각) | She came up with a great idea. |\n| come down to | 결국 다가옴 (귀결) | It comes down to money. |\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I'll come to your house. (전화 통화 중, 내가 상대 집에) → (O) 맞음. 화자가 상대 쪽으로 가니까 come.\n- (X) Come to here. → (O) Come here. (here에 to 안 씀)\n- (X) The book came out from last week. → (O) The book came out last week.\n\n## 연습\n\n1. Something _____ up, so I have to cancel. (came / went)\n2. She _____ across an interesting article online. (came / got)\n3. The total _____ to $120. (comes / gets)\n4. Can you _____ over after work? (come / go)\n5. He _____ up with a solution in 5 minutes. (came / made)\n\n**정답**: 1. came  2. came  3. comes  4. come  5. came"}, {"name": "08-put", "content": "# put\n\n> **핵심 감각: 놓다** — 특정 위치나 상태에 배치하는 것\n\n## 핵심 감각\n\nput의 모든 뜻은 **\"놓다\"** 하나로 통한다. 물건을 테이블에, 사람을 곤란한 상황에, 생각을 말에, 돈을 주식에 — 어디에 놓느냐에 따라 해석이 달라질 뿐이다.\n\n## 감각 갈래\n\n### 물건을 어딘가에 놓으면 → 두다 / 놓다 ★★★★★\n가장 기본. 물건을 특정 위치에 배치하는 것.\n- Put your bag on the table.\n- Where did you put my keys?\n\n### 사람을 상태에 놓으면 → 처하게 하다 ★★★★★\n사람이나 사물을 어떤 상태에 배치하는 것.\n- You're putting me in a difficult position.\n- Put yourself in my shoes.\n\n### 생각을 말에 놓으면 → 표현하다 ★★★★\n머릿속 생각을 말이라는 자리에 배치하는 것.\n- How should I put it?\n- To put it simply, we need more time.\n\n### 돈·노력을 어딘가에 놓으면 → 투자하다 / 투입하다 ★★★\n시간·돈·에너지를 특정 대상에 배치하는 것.\n- She puts a lot of effort into her work.\n- He put all his money into stocks.\n\n## 필수 패턴\n| 패턴 | 감각 | 예문 |\n|------|------|------|\n| put on | 몸 위에 놓음 (입다) | Put on your jacket. |\n| put off | 뒤로 놓음 (미루다) | Don't put off your homework. |\n| put out | 밖으로 놓음 (끄다) | Put out the fire! |\n| put up with | 위에 올려놓고 버팀 (참다) | I can't put up with this noise. |\n| put away | 치워서 놓음 | Put away your toys. |\n| put down | 아래에 놓음 / 깎아내림 | He always puts me down. |\n| put together | 합쳐서 놓음 (조립) | Let's put together a plan. |\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I put my coat. → (O) I put on my coat. (입다는 반드시 on 필요)\n- (X) I putted it there. → (O) I put it there. (put-put-put 불규칙)\n- (X) Don't put off to do it. → (O) Don't put off doing it. (put off + -ing)\n\n## 연습\n\n1. _____ on a sweater. It's cold outside. (Put / Get)\n2. She keeps _____ off the meeting. (putting / taking)\n3. I can't _____ up with his attitude anymore. (put / keep)\n4. To _____ it simply, the answer is no. (put / make)\n5. He _____ all his energy into the project. (put / gave)\n\n**정답**: 1. Put  2. putting  3. put  4. put  5. put"}, {"name": "09-keep", "content": "# keep\n\n> **핵심 감각: 유지** — 변하지 않게 붙잡아 두는 것\n\n## 핵심 감각\n\nkeep의 모든 뜻은 **\"유지\"** 하나로 통한다. 행동을, 상태를, 약속을, 동물을 — 변하지 않게 계속 그대로 두는 것. 뭘 유지하느냐에 따라 해석이 달라질 뿐이다.\n\n## 감각 갈래\n\n### 행동을 유지하면 → 계속 ~하다 ★★★★★\n멈추지 않고 이어가는 것. 가장 많이 쓰는 용법.\n- Keep going. Don't stop.\n- She keeps talking during the movie.\n\n### 상태·물건을 유지하면 → 보관하다 / 그대로 두다 ★★★★★\n상태나 물건을 변하지 않게 두는 것.\n- Keep the change.\n- Keep your room clean.\n\n### 약속·비밀을 유지하면 → 지키다 ★★★\n변하지 않게 이행하는 것.\n- Can you keep a secret?\n- He always keeps his promises.\n\n### 동물·습관을 유지하면 → 기르다 / 보유하다 ★★★\n지속적으로 가지고 있는 것.\n- She keeps a diary.\n- They keep chickens in the backyard.\n\n## 필수 패턴\n| 패턴 | 감각 | 예문 |\n|------|------|------|\n| keep + -ing | 행동을 유지 | Keep trying. You'll get it. |\n| keep + 목적어 + 형용사 | 상태를 유지 | Keep the door open. |\n| keep up with | 속도를 유지 (따라감) | I can't keep up with the news. |\n| keep on | 계속을 유지 (강조) | He kept on interrupting me. |\n| keep out | 바깥 상태를 유지 | Keep out! Danger zone. |\n| keep away from | 거리를 유지 | Keep away from the edge. |\n\n## 함정\n- (X) Keep to study hard. → (O) Keep studying hard. (keep + -ing)\n- (X) I keep it secret. → (O) I'll keep it a secret. (관사 필요)\n- (X) Keep going on. → (O) Keep going. 또는 Keep on going. (중복 주의)\n\n## 연습\n\n1. _____ going. You're almost there. (Keep / Stay)\n2. She _____ the door locked at all times. (keeps / puts)\n3. I can't _____ up with all the changes. (keep / get)\n4. He always _____ his word. (keeps / holds)\n5. _____ away from that dog. It bites. (Keep / Go)\n\n**정답**: 1. Keep  2. keeps  3. keep  4. keeps  5. Keep"}, {"name": "10-turn", "content": "# turn\n\n> **핵심 감각: 방향 전환** — 현재 방향에서 다른 방향으로 돌리는 것\n\n## 핵심 감각\n\nturn의 모든 뜻은 **\"방향 전환\"** 하나로 통한다. 몸을 돌리든, 상태가 바뀌든, 스위치를 돌리든, 페이지를 넘기든 — 지금 향하던 방향에서 다른 방향으로 돌리는 것. 뭘 돌리느냐에 따라 해석이 달라질 뿐이다.\n\n## 감각 갈래\n\n### 몸·방향을 돌리면 → 돌다 / 회전하다 ★★★★★\n가장 기본. 물리적으로 방향을 바꾸는 것.\n- Turn left at the next light.\n- She turned around and waved.\n\n### 상태의 방향을 돌리면 → 변하다 / ~이 되다 ★★★★★\n한 상태에서 다른 상태로 전환되는 것.\n- The leaves turn red in autumn.\n- He turned 30 last week.\n\n### 스위치를 돌리면 → 켜다 / 끄다 ★★★★\n스위치를 돌리는 물리적 감각에서 확장.\n- Turn on the TV.\n- Turn off the lights before you leave.\n\n### 페이지를 돌리면 → 넘기다 ★★★\n종이를 물리적으로 돌리는 것.\n- Turn to page 42.\n- She turned the page slowly.\n\n## 필수 패턴\n| 패턴 | 감각 | 예문 |\n|------|------|------|\n| turn on | 켜는 방향으로 | Turn on the air conditioner. |\n| turn off | 끄는 방향으로 | Can you turn off the music? |\n| turn up | 위 방향으로 (나타남/볼륨↑) | He turned up late to the meeting. |\n| turn down | 아래 방향으로 (거절/볼륨↓) | She turned down the offer. |\n| turn out | 밖으로 드러남 (결과) | It turned out to be a great movie. |\n| turn into | 안으로 전환 (변신) | The frog turned into a prince. |\n| turn around | 반대로 전환 (호전) | The company turned around in 2 years. |\n\n## 함정\n- (X) The light turned on. → (O) 맞음. 하지만 \"내가 켰다\"면 I turned on the light.\n- (X) She turned down to the offer. → (O) She turned down the offer. (to 불필요)\n- (X) It turned out being great. → (O) It turned out to be great.\n\n## 연습\n\n1. _____ left at the corner and you'll see it. (Turn / Go)\n2. The weather _____ cold overnight. (turned / got)\n3. It _____ out that she was right all along. (turned / came)\n4. Can you _____ down the volume? (turn / put)\n5. He _____ down the job offer. (turned / gave)\n\n**정답**: 1. Turn  2. turned  3. turned  4. turn  5. turned"}, {"name": "11-bring", "content": "# bring\n\n> **핵심 감각: 가져오다** — 화자 쪽으로 끌고 오는 것. take의 정반대.\n\n## 핵심 감각\n\nbring의 모든 뜻은 **\"가져오다\"** 하나로 통한다. take가 \"내게서 멀어지게 취하다\"면 bring은 \"나에게 가까이 끌고 오다\". 물건이든, 결과든, 화제든 — 뭘 가져오느냐에 따라 해석이 달라질 뿐이다.\n\n## 감각 갈래\n\n### 물건·사람을 가져오면 → 데려오다 / 가져오다 ★★★★★\n가장 기본. 화자 쪽으로 이동시키는 것. take와 방향이 반대.\n- Bring your friends to the party.\n- Can you bring me a glass of water?\n\n### 결과·상태를 가져오면 → 초래하다 / 가져다주다 ★★★★\n결과나 변화를 이쪽으로 끌고 오는 것.\n- The new policy brought many changes.\n- Music brings me joy.\n\n### 화제를 가져오면 → 꺼내다 / 언급하다 ★★★\n대화의 장으로 주제를 끌고 오는 것.\n- She brought up an interesting point.\n- Don't bring that topic up again.\n\n## 필수 패턴\n| 패턴 | 감각 | 예문 |\n|------|------|------|\n| bring up | 위로 가져옴 (화제/양육) | He was brought up in a small town. |\n| bring out | 밖으로 가져옴 (드러냄) | The seasoning brings out the flavor. |\n| bring back | 되돌려 가져옴 (되살림) | This song brings back memories. |\n| bring about | 결과를 가져옴 (야기) | What brought about the change? |\n| bring down | 아래로 가져옴 (끌어내림) | The scandal brought down the CEO. |\n| bring together | 함께 가져옴 (모음) | The event brought people together. |\n\n## bring vs take\n- **bring**: 화자/청자 쪽으로 → \"이리로 가져와\"\n- **take**: 화자에게서 멀어지는 방향 → \"저리로 가져가\"\n- Bring an umbrella (when you come here). / Take an umbrella (when you go there).\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I'll bring it to there. → (O) I'll take it there. (상대방 쪽은 take)\n- (X) She brought up by her grandparents. → (O) She was brought up by her grandparents. (수동태)\n- (X) Bring me to the station. → (O) Take me to the station. (화자가 같이 가면 take)\n\n## 연습\n\n1. _____ your laptop to the meeting. (Bring / Take)\n2. This photo _____ back so many memories. (brings / takes)\n3. She was _____ up in the countryside. (brought / grown)\n4. Don't _____ up that subject again. (bring / take)\n5. The crisis _____ about major reforms. (brought / made)\n\n**정답**: 1. Bring  2. brings  3. brought  4. bring  5. brought"}, {"name": "12-hold", "content": "# hold\n\n> **핵심 감각: 잡고 놓지 않다** — 쥐고 있는 상태를 유지하는 것\n\n## 핵심 감각\n\nhold의 모든 뜻은 **\"잡고 놓지 않다\"** 하나로 통한다. 손에 든 물건이든, 위치든, 행사든, 감정이든, 전화든 — 놓지 않고 쥐고 있는 것. 뭘 잡고 있느냐에 따라 해석이 달라질 뿐이다.\n\n## 감각 갈래\n\n### 물건을 잡고 있으면 → 들다 / 쥐다 ★★★★★\n가장 기본. 손에 쥐고 놓지 않는 물리적 감각.\n- Hold my hand.\n- She was holding a cup of coffee.\n\n### 상태·위치를 잡고 있으면 → 유지하다 / 지탱하다 ★★★★★\n변하지 않게 잡아두는 것.\n- Hold your position.\n- The bridge can hold 10 tons.\n\n### 행사를 잡고 있으면 → 개최하다 / 열다 ★★★★\n행사를 잡아서 진행하는 것.\n- The meeting will be held on Friday.\n- They hold a festival every summer.\n\n### 감정을 잡고 있으면 → 참다 / 억제하다 ★★★\n터져 나오려는 것을 놓지 않고 잡아두는 것.\n- Hold your breath.\n- I couldn't hold back my tears.\n\n### 상황을 잡고 있으면 → 대기하다 ★★★\n전화나 상황에서 놓지 않고 기다리는 것.\n- Please hold. I'll transfer your call.\n- Hold on a second.\n\n## 필수 패턴\n| 패턴 | 감각 | 예문 |\n|------|------|------|\n| hold on | 놓지 않고 기다림 | Hold on, let me check. |\n| hold up | 위로 잡아 올림 (지연/버팀) | Sorry, I was held up in traffic. |\n| hold back | 뒤로 잡아둠 (억제) | She held back her anger. |\n| hold off | 떨어뜨려 잡아둠 (보류) | Let's hold off on the decision. |\n| hold out | 밖으로 잡아둠 (버팀) | How long can you hold out? |\n| hold onto | 꽉 잡고 놓지 않음 | Hold onto the railing. |\n| hold together | 함께 잡아둠 (결속) | She holds the team together. |\n\n## 함정\n- (X) Hold the line, please. → (O) 맞음. 전화에서 자연스러운 표현.\n- (X) The concert held last night. → (O) The concert was held last night. (수동태)\n- (X) I holded it tightly. → (O) I held it tightly. (hold-held-held 불규칙)\n\n## 연습\n\n1. _____ on a second. I'll be right back. (Hold / Wait)\n2. The event will be _____ at the main hall. (held / holded)\n3. She couldn't _____ back her tears. (hold / keep)\n4. Traffic _____ us up for an hour. (held / took)\n5. _____ onto your ticket. You'll need it later. (Hold / Keep)\n\n**정답**: 1. Hold  2. held  3. hold  4. held  5. Hold"}, {"name": "13-in", "content": "# in\n\n> 어떤 경계 '안에' 들어가 있다\n\n## 감각 확장: 공간 → 시간 → 추상\n\n### 공간: 경계 안\n닫힌 공간 속에 존재하는 감각.\n- The keys are in my pocket.\n- She's in the kitchen.\n\n### 시간: 범위 안\n넓은 시간 덩어리 속에 있는 감각. 월, 연도, 기간.\n- I was born in 1990.\n- I'll be back in 10 minutes. (10분 후 = 10분이라는 시간 안에)\n\n### 추상: 상태·수단 안\n보이지 않는 경계 안에 있는 감각.\n- She's in trouble. / He's in love.\n- Say it in English. / Pay in cash.\n\n## 동사 조합 TOP\n| 동사 + in | 감각 | 예문 |\n|-----------|------|------|\n| get in | 안으로 들어가다 | Get in the car. |\n| come in | 들어오다 | Come in and sit down. |\n| put in | 넣다 / 투입하다 | She put in a lot of hours. |\n| give in | 굴복하다 | He finally gave in. |\n| turn in | 제출하다 / 잠자리 들다 | Turn in your assignment by Friday. |\n| bring in | 도입하다 | They brought in a new policy. |\n\n## vs at\n- **in**: 경계 안 (넓은 공간) — in Seoul, in the room\n- **at**: 한 점 (좁은 지점) — at the station, at home\n\n## 함정\n- (X) in the morning / (X) on the morning → (O) in the morning (아침이라는 시간 덩어리 안)\n- (X) in Monday → (O) on Monday (요일은 on)\n- (X) arrive in the airport → (O) arrive at the airport (지점은 at)\n\n## 연습\n1. She lives _____ a small town. (in / at)\n2. I'll see you _____ 30 minutes. (in / after)\n3. He's _____ trouble with the boss. (in / on)\n4. Get _____ the car. We're leaving. (in / on)\n5. The meeting is _____ March. (in / on)\n\n**정답**: 1. in  2. in  3. in  4. in  5. in"}, {"name": "14-out", "content": "# out\n\n> 경계 '밖으로' 나온다\n\n## 감각 확장: 공간 → 출현 → 소멸 → 완료\n\n### 공간: 밖으로\n안에서 바깥으로 나오는 감각.\n- Get out of the house!\n- She walked out of the room.\n\n### 출현·드러남\n숨어있던 것이 밖으로 나와 보이는 감각.\n- The truth came out.\n- It turns out he was lying.\n\n### 소멸·소진\n다 나가서 없어지는 감각.\n- We ran out of milk.\n- The fire went out.\n\n### 완료·끝까지\n안에 있던 걸 전부 꺼내는 → 끝까지 하는 감각.\n- Figure out the answer. (끝까지 알아내다)\n- Work out a solution. (끝까지 해결하다)\n\n## 동사 조합 TOP\n| 동사 + out | 감각 | 예문 |\n|------------|------|------|\n| get out | 나가다 | Get out of here! |\n| find out | 알아내다 | I need to find out the truth. |\n| turn out | 결과가 ~이 되다 | It turned out fine. |\n| go out | 나가다 / 꺼지다 | The lights went out. |\n| take out | 꺼내다 | Take out your wallet. |\n| make out | 알아보다 | I can't make out the sign. |\n| hold out | 버티다 | Hold out a little longer. |\n\n## vs off\n- **out**: 안에서 밖으로 나옴 — go out (밖으로 나가다)\n- **off**: 표면에서 떨어져 나옴 — go off (울리다/폭발하다)\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I ran out milk. → (O) I ran out of milk. (of 필요)\n- (X) Find out it. → (O) Find it out. 또는 Find out the answer. (대명사는 사이에)\n- (X) The secret came out to everyone. → (O) The secret came out. (to 불필요)\n\n## 연습\n1. We _____ out of time. Hurry up! (ran / went)\n2. She finally _____ out what happened. (found / got)\n3. It _____ out to be easier than I thought. (turned / came)\n4. _____ out your homework and put it on the desk. (Take / Put)\n5. The candle _____ out in the wind. (went / turned)\n\n**정답**: 1. ran  2. found  3. turned  4. Take  5. went"}, {"name": "15-on", "content": "# on\n\n> 표면에 '접촉'하고 있다 — 붙어있으니까 계속된다\n\n## 감각 확장: 접촉 → 진행 → 작동 → 주제\n\n### 접촉: 표면 위\n무언가에 닿아서 붙어있는 감각.\n- The book is on the table.\n- There's a stain on your shirt.\n\n### 진행: 계속됨\n표면에 붙어있으면 떨어지지 않는다 → 멈추지 않고 이어진다.\n- Keep on going. Don't stop.\n- Go on. What happened next?\n- The show must go on.\n\n### 작동: 켜져 있음\n스위치가 \"붙어있는\" 감각 → 작동 중.\n- Turn on the light.\n- Is the AC on?\n- The TV has been on all day.\n\n### 주제·대상\n관심이 그 위에 \"올려져 있는\" 감각.\n- a book on history\n- We agreed on the plan.\n\n### 날짜·요일\n특정한 날 위에 있는 감각. (in이 넓은 시간이면 on은 좁은 날)\n- on Monday / on Christmas Day\n- on the morning of July 4th\n\n### 의존·기반\n무언가 위에 서 있는 → 그것에 기대는 감각.\n- It depends on you.\n- The economy runs on oil.\n\n## 동사 조합 TOP\n| 동사 + on | 감각 | 예문 |\n|-----------|------|------|\n| go on | 계속하다 | Go on. I'm listening. |\n| keep on | 계속하다 (강조) | She kept on talking. |\n| turn on | 켜다 | Turn on the heater. |\n| hold on | 기다리다 / 붙잡다 | Hold on a minute. |\n| put on | 입다 / 올려놓다 | Put on your shoes. |\n| come on | 어서 / 힘내 | Come on, we're late! |\n| take on | 떠맡다 | He took on a new role. |\n\n## vs in\n- **on**: 표면 접촉 — on the wall (벽 위에 붙어있음)\n- **in**: 내부 포함 — in the wall (벽 속에 묻혀있음)\n\n## 함정\n- (X) on the bus / on the train → (O) 맞음! 대중교통은 on (표면 위에 서 있으니까)\n- (X) in Monday → (O) on Monday (요일은 on)\n- (X) I depend on to him. → (O) I depend on him.\n\n## 연습\n1. Keep _____ trying. You'll get better. (on / in)\n2. She put _____ her coat and left. (on / in)\n3. The meeting is _____ Friday. (on / in)\n4. It depends _____ the weather. (on / in)\n5. Is the air conditioner _____? (on / in)\n\n**정답**: 1. on  2. on  3. on  4. on  5. on"}, {"name": "16-off", "content": "# off\n\n> 표면에서 '떨어져 나간다' — on의 반대, 분리와 중단\n\n## 감각 확장: 분리 → 중단 → 완료 → 출발\n\n### 분리: 떨어짐\n붙어있던 것이 떨어져 나가는 감각.\n- The button fell off my shirt.\n- Take off your shoes at the door.\n\n### 중단: 끄기\n작동이 \"떨어지는\" → 멈추는 감각.\n- Turn off the TV.\n- The meeting was called off.\n\n### 완료: 해치움\n떨어뜨려서 끝내는 감각.\n- Pay off your debt.\n- She finished off the last piece of cake.\n\n### 출발: 떠남\n\"여기서 떨어져 나가는\" → 출발.\n- We're off to Paris tomorrow.\n- The plane takes off at 9.\n\n### 할인: 깎아냄\n가격에서 떨어뜨리는 감각.\n- 20% off everything today.\n- Can you take $10 off?\n\n## 동사 조합 TOP\n| 동사 + off | 감각 | 예문 |\n|------------|------|------|\n| take off | 벗다 / 이륙 / 떠나다 | The plane took off on time. |\n| turn off | 끄다 | Turn off the lights. |\n| put off | 미루다 | Don't put off your work. |\n| go off | 울리다 / 폭발 | The alarm went off. |\n| get off | 내리다 | Get off at the next stop. |\n| hold off | 보류하다 | Let's hold off for now. |\n| give off | 발산하다 | Roses give off a sweet smell. |\n\n## vs out\n- **off**: 표면에서 떨어짐 — turn off (끄다, 스위치에서 떨어짐)\n- **out**: 안에서 밖으로 — go out (밖으로 나가다)\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I get off from the bus. → (O) I get off the bus. (from 불필요)\n- (X) The meeting called off. → (O) The meeting was called off. (수동태)\n- (X) Turn off it. → (O) Turn it off. (대명사는 사이에)\n\n## 연습\n1. Please _____ off your phone during the movie. (turn / put)\n2. The plane _____ off 30 minutes late. (took / got)\n3. She _____ off the meeting until next week. (put / held)\n4. Everything is 30% _____ today. (off / down)\n5. The fire alarm _____ off at midnight. (went / turned)\n\n**정답**: 1. turn  2. took  3. put  4. off  5. went"}, {"name": "17-up", "content": "# up\n\n> '위로' 올라간다 — 그리고 끝까지 올라가면 '완료'가 된다\n\n## 감각 확장: 위로 → 완료 → 증가 → 출현 → 시작\n\n### 위로: 물리적 상승\n아래에서 위로 올라가는 감각.\n- Stand up, please.\n- Look up at the sky.\n\n### 완료: 끝까지\n위로 올라가서 꼭대기에 도달 → 다 끝남. **네이티브가 가장 많이 쓰는 감각.**\n- Eat up your vegetables. (다 먹어)\n- Drink up. We have to go. (다 마셔)\n- Use up all the paper. (다 써버리다)\n- Time's up! (시간 끝!)\n\n### 증가: 올라감\n수치·강도가 위로 올라가는 감각.\n- Turn up the volume.\n- Speed up. We're late.\n\n### 출현: 나타남\n아래에서 위로 올라와 보이는 감각.\n- Something came up. (일이 생겼어)\n- She showed up late. (나타났다)\n\n### 시작·준비\n아래에서 일으켜 세우는 감각.\n- Set up the equipment.\n- Warm up before you exercise.\n\n### 분할·해체\n조각조각 올려서 분리하는 감각.\n- Break up the chocolate into pieces.\n- They broke up last month. (헤어지다)\n\n## 동사 조합 TOP\n| 동사 + up | 감각 | 예문 |\n|-----------|------|------|\n| get up | 일어나다 | I get up at 6 every day. |\n| give up | 포기하다 | Don't give up. |\n| make up | 화해 / 구성 / 꾸미다 | Let's make up. |\n| come up | 다가오다 / 생기다 | A problem came up. |\n| bring up | 화제 꺼내다 / 키우다 | Don't bring up that topic. |\n| keep up | 따라가다 | Keep up the good work. |\n| turn up | 나타나다 / 올리다 | He finally turned up. |\n| hold up | 지연시키다 / 버티다 | What's holding things up? |\n\n## vs out (완료 감각 비교)\n- **up**: 끝까지 채워서 완료 — eat up (다 먹다), fill up (다 채우다)\n- **out**: 다 빠져나가서 완료 — run out (다 떨어지다), burn out (다 타다)\n\n## 함정\n- (X) Wake up! → (O) 맞음. 가장 자연스러운 표현.\n- (X) I showed up to late. → (O) I showed up late. (to 불필요)\n- (X) Pick up it. → (O) Pick it up. (대명사는 사이에)\n\n## 연습\n1. Hurry _____! We're going to miss the bus. (up / on)\n2. She _____ up a great idea. (came up with / made up with)\n3. Time's _____. Put down your pens. (up / out)\n4. He _____ up late to the meeting again. (showed / turned) — 둘 다 가능\n5. _____ up before you run. (Warm / Heat)\n\n**정답**: 1. up  2. came up with  3. up  4. showed/turned  5. Warm"}, {"name": "18-down", "content": "# down\n\n> '아래로' 내려간다 — 감소, 안정, 기록의 감각\n\n## 감각 확장: 아래로 → 감소 → 기록 → 안정 → 중단 → 거절\n\n### 아래로: 물리적 하강\n위에서 아래로 내려오는 감각.\n- Sit down, please.\n- Put it down on the table.\n\n### 감소: 줄어듦\n수치나 강도가 내려가는 감각.\n- Slow down. You're driving too fast.\n- Calm down. It's going to be okay.\n- Turn down the volume.\n\n### 기록: 적어 내림\n머릿속에서 종이 위로 \"내려놓는\" 감각.\n- Write down your phone number.\n- Let me note that down.\n\n### 안정·고정: 자리 잡음\n아래로 내려와서 움직이지 않는 감각.\n- Settle down and focus.\n- Pin down the details.\n\n### 중단·폐쇄: 멈춤\n아래로 내려서 작동을 멈추는 감각.\n- The system shut down.\n- The factory broke down.\n\n### 거절: 내려놓음\n제안을 아래로 내리는 감각.\n- She turned down the offer.\n- He let me down. (실망시키다)\n\n## 동사 조합 TOP\n| 동사 + down | 감각 | 예문 |\n|-------------|------|------|\n| sit down | 앉다 | Please sit down. |\n| turn down | 거절 / 볼륨 낮추기 | She turned down the job. |\n| break down | 고장 / 무너지다 | My car broke down. |\n| calm down | 진정하다 | Calm down and listen. |\n| put down | 내려놓다 / 비하 | Put down your phone. |\n| write down | 적다 | Write down the address. |\n| come down to | 결국 ~에 달려 있다 | It comes down to money. |\n\n## vs up\n- **down**: 감소·안정·기록 — calm down, write down\n- **up**: 증가·완료·출현 — speed up, eat up\n\n## 함정\n- (X) Turn down it. → (O) Turn it down. (대명사는 사이에)\n- (X) She broke down her car. → (O) Her car broke down. (자동사)\n- (X) Write down it. → (O) Write it down.\n\n## 연습\n1. Can you _____ down the music? (turn / put)\n2. She _____ down and started to cry. (broke / turned)\n3. _____ down your name and email. (Write / Put)\n4. The kids need to _____ down before bed. (calm / slow)\n5. He _____ me down when I needed him most. (let / put)\n\n**정답**: 1. turn  2. broke  3. Write  4. calm  5. let"}, {"name": "19-over", "content": "# over\n\n> 아치형으로 '넘어간다' — 끝까지 넘어가면 종료, 다시 돌아오면 반복\n\n## 감각 확장: 공간 → 종료 → 반복 → 초과\n\n### 공간: 위를 넘어\n장애물 위를 아치형으로 넘어가는 감각.\n- The cat jumped over the fence.\n- She leaned over the balcony.\n\n### 종료: 끝남\n완전히 넘어가서 끝나는 감각.\n- The game is over.\n- I'm glad it's over.\n\n### 반복: 다시 넘기\n처음으로 돌아가서 다시 넘는 감각.\n- Let's start over.\n- Can you do it over?\n\n### 초과·전체\n경계를 넘는 → 넘치는 감각.\n- She's over 40.\n- I've been thinking it over. (이리저리 전체를)\n\n## 동사 조합 TOP\n| 동사 + over | 감각 | 예문 |\n|-------------|------|------|\n| get over | 넘어서 극복하다 | Get over it. It's not a big deal. |\n| go over | 넘어가며 검토하다 | Let's go over the plan again. |\n| take over | 넘겨받다 | She took over the project. |\n| turn over | 뒤집다 | Turn over the page. |\n| come over | 넘어와 방문하다 | Come over to my place. |\n| hand over | 넘겨주다 | Hand over the documents. |\n\n## vs above\n- **over**: 위를 넘어가는 동적 감각 — jump over\n- **above**: 위에 떠 있는 정적 감각 — above the clouds\n\n## 함정\n- (X) The game is over already? → (O) 맞음. 자연스러운 표현.\n- (X) I need to get over from my cold. → (O) I need to get over my cold. (from 불필요)\n\n## 연습\n1. The meeting is _____. You can leave. (over / out)\n2. Let's go _____ the details one more time. (over / through)\n3. She got _____ her fear of heights. (over / out)\n4. Can we start _____? I made a mistake. (over / up)\n5. He _____ over the company last year. (took / got)\n\n**정답**: 1. over  2. over  3. over  4. over  5. took"}, {"name": "20-through", "content": "# through\n\n> 처음부터 끝까지 '뚫고 지나간다' — 관통, 경험, 완수\n\n## 감각 확장: 공간 → 경험 → 완수\n\n### 공간: 관통\n한쪽에서 반대쪽으로 뚫고 지나가는 감각.\n- We drove through the tunnel.\n- Light shines through the window.\n\n### 경험: 겪다\n어려움을 처음부터 끝까지 뚫고 지나가는 감각.\n- She went through a difficult divorce.\n- I've been through a lot this year.\n\n### 완수: 끝까지\n시작점에서 끝점까지 관통하여 마무리하는 감각.\n- Read the book all the way through.\n- Follow through on your promises.\n\n### 매개: 수단\n무언가를 \"통해서\" 도달하는 감각.\n- I found the job through a friend.\n- You can apply through the website.\n\n## 동사 조합 TOP\n| 동사 + through | 감각 | 예문 |\n|----------------|------|------|\n| go through | 겪다 / 통과하다 | He's going through a tough time. |\n| get through | 끝내다 / 연결되다 | I can't get through to her phone. |\n| come through | 해내다 / 도착하다 | He always comes through in a crisis. |\n| break through | 돌파하다 | They broke through the enemy lines. |\n| see through | 꿰뚫어 보다 | I can see through his lies. |\n| put through | 연결하다 / 겪게 하다 | I'll put you through to the manager. |\n\n## vs across\n- **through**: 안을 뚫고 지나감 — through the forest (숲 안을 관통)\n- **across**: 표면을 가로지름 — across the field (들판을 가로질러)\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I went through from a hard time. → (O) I went through a hard time.\n- (X) Read through of the document. → (O) Read through the document.\n\n## 연습\n1. She went _____ all the files carefully. (through / over)\n2. I got the job _____ a friend. (through / by)\n3. We need to get _____ this week somehow. (through / over)\n4. He can see _____ your excuses. (through / out)\n5. Follow _____ on what you started. (through / up)\n\n**정답**: 1. through  2. through  3. through  4. through  5. through"}, {"name": "21-across", "content": "# across\n\n> 평면을 '가로질러' 반대편으로\n\n## 감각 확장\n### 공간: 가로질러\n- She walked across the street.\n- The bridge goes across the river.\n\n### 우연히 만남: 가로지르다가 마주침\n- I came across an old friend at the store.\n- She ran across an interesting article.\n\n### 전달·이해: 반대편에 도달\n- Did the message get across?\n- She got her point across clearly.\n\n## 동사 조합 TOP\n| 동사 + across | 감각 | 예문 |\n|come across|우연히 발견|I came across this book by accident.|\n|get across|전달하다|How do I get my idea across?|\n|run across|우연히 만나다|I ran across her at the mall.|\n|cut across|가로지르다|Let's cut across the park.|\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I came across with a problem. → (O) I came across a problem.\n\n## 연습\n1. She _____ across an old photo in the drawer. (came / went)\n2. Did the meaning get _____ to the audience? (across / through)\n3. They walked _____ the bridge at sunset. (across / through)\n\n**정답**: 1. came  2. across  3. across"}, {"name": "22-along", "content": "# along\n\n> 길을 따라 '나란히' — 동반과 진행\n\n## 감각 확장\n### 공간: ~을 따라\n- Walk along the river.\n- There are trees along the road.\n\n### 동반: 함께\n- Come along! We're leaving.\n- Bring your friends along.\n\n### 진행: 나아감\n- The project is moving along nicely.\n- How are you getting along?\n\n## 동사 조합 TOP\n| 동사 + along | 감각 | 예문 |\n|get along|잘 지내다|Do you get along with your coworkers?|\n|come along|함께 오다 / 진행되다|Things are coming along well.|\n|go along with|동의하다|I'll go along with your plan.|\n|move along|이동하다|Move along, nothing to see here.|\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I get along him. → (O) I get along with him. (with 필요)\n\n## 연습\n1. She gets _____ well with everyone. (along / on)\n2. The work is coming _____ nicely. (along / up)\n3. Walk _____ the path until you see the sign. (along / through)\n\n**정답**: 1. along  2. along  3. along"}, {"name": "23-around", "content": "# around\n\n> 둥글게 '주변을' — 주위, 여기저기, 대략, 존재\n\n## 감각 확장\n### 공간: 주위에 / 여기저기\n- Look around. It's beautiful here.\n- She traveled around Europe.\n\n### 대략\n- There were around 50 people.\n- I'll be there around 3.\n\n### 존재: 근처에 있음\n- Is Tom around?\n- He's been around for a long time.\n\n### 회피: 둘러감\n- We need to get around this problem.\n- There's no way around it.\n\n## 동사 조합 TOP\n| 동사 + around | 감각 | 예문 |\n|get around|돌아다니다 / 회피|How do you get around the city?|\n|come around|들르다 / 마음 바꾸다|She'll come around eventually.|\n|turn around|돌아서다 / 호전|The company turned around in a year.|\n|hang around|어슬렁거리다|Stop hanging around and do something.|\n\n## 함정\n- (X) around about 50 → (O) around 50 (중복)\n\n## 연습\n1. There were _____ 200 guests at the wedding. (around / about) — 둘 다 가능\n2. Is your manager _____? (around / here) — 둘 다 가능\n3. We need to find a way _____ this issue. (around / through)\n\n**정답**: 1. around/about  2. around/here  3. around"}, {"name": "24-away", "content": "# away\n\n> 여기서 '멀어진다' — 거리, 사라짐, 몰두\n\n## 감각 확장\n### 거리: 멀어짐\n- Go away! Leave me alone.\n- The store is 5 minutes away.\n\n### 사라짐: 없어짐\n- The pain went away.\n- She gave away all her old clothes.\n\n### 몰두: 계속 (멀리 가듯 빠져듦)\n- She was typing away all afternoon.\n- They chatted away for hours.\n\n### 보관: 치워둠\n- Put away your toys.\n- She locked away the jewelry.\n\n## 동사 조합 TOP\n| 동사 + away | 감각 | 예문 |\n|go away|떠나다 / 사라지다|The headache won't go away.|\n|give away|나눠주다 / 누설|Don't give away the ending.|\n|take away|가져가다 / 빼앗다|Nothing can take away this memory.|\n|put away|치우다|Put away your phone during dinner.|\n|run away|도망치다|The dog ran away from home.|\n|get away|탈출하다|I need to get away for a few days.|\n\n## 함정\n- (X) Go to away. → (O) Go away. (to 불필요)\n- (X) She threw away it. → (O) She threw it away.\n\n## 연습\n1. The noise won't go _____. (away / off)\n2. She _____ away her old books. (gave / put)\n3. We need to get _____ from the city. (away / out)\n\n**정답**: 1. away  2. gave  3. away"}, {"name": "25-back", "content": "# back\n\n> 원래 자리로 '되돌아간다' — 복귀, 반환, 과거\n\n## 감각 확장\n### 복귀: 돌아옴\n- I'll be back in 10 minutes.\n- Welcome back!\n\n### 반환: 돌려줌\n- Give back my pen.\n- I need to pay back the loan.\n\n### 과거: 되돌아봄\n- Looking back, it was a great decision.\n- That takes me back to my childhood.\n\n### 보복: 되갚음\n- I'll get back at him for this.\n- She fought back.\n\n## 동사 조합 TOP\n| 동사 + back | 감각 | 예문 |\n|come back|돌아오다|When will you come back?|\n|give back|돌려주다|Give it back to me.|\n|get back|돌아가다 / 되찾다|I need to get back to work.|\n|hold back|참다 / 억제하다|She held back her tears.|\n|take back|취소하다 / 돌려받다|I take back what I said.|\n|look back|되돌아보다|Don't look back. Move forward.|\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I'll call back to you. → (O) I'll call you back.\n- (X) Give back it. → (O) Give it back.\n\n## 연습\n1. She'll be _____ by 5 o'clock. (back / around)\n2. I want to get my money _____. (back / out)\n3. He took _____ his words. (back / off)\n\n**정답**: 1. back  2. back  3. back"}, {"name": "26-to", "content": "# to\n\n> '향하는 지점' — 영어에서 가장 기본적인 방향 감각\n\n## 감각 확장\n### 방향·도착점\n- I'm going to the office.\n- She talked to her boss.\n\n### 결과·변화\n- It led to a disaster.\n- She grew up to be a doctor.\n\n### 비교\n- I prefer coffee to tea.\n- Compared to last year, sales are up.\n\n### 시간 한계\n- It's 10 to 3. (3시 10분 전)\n- Monday to Friday.\n\n## 동사 조합\n| 패턴 | 예문 |\n|get to|I finally got to meet her.|\n|come to|The bill comes to $80.|\n|turn to|She turned to me for help.|\n|belong to|This book belongs to me.|\n|lead to|Hard work leads to success.|\n\n## vs for\n- **to**: 도착점 — go to the store\n- **for**: 목적·위함 — go for a walk\n\n## 연습\n1. She went _____ the hospital. (to / for)\n2. This leads _____ only one conclusion. (to / for)\n3. I prefer tea _____ coffee. (to / than)\n\n**정답**: 1. to  2. to  3. to"}, {"name": "27-from", "content": "# from\n\n> '출발점' — 어디서부터인지, to의 반대\n\n## 감각 확장\n### 출발점\n- I'm from Korea.\n- The train departs from platform 3.\n\n### 원인·근거\n- She suffers from allergies.\n- I know from experience.\n\n### 분리·차이\n- This is different from that.\n- Keep him away from trouble.\n\n### 재료·출처\n- Wine is made from grapes.\n- A quote from the book.\n\n## 동사 조합\n| 패턴 | 예문 |\n|come from|Where do you come from?|\n|get from|I got this from a friend.|\n|keep from|I can't keep from laughing.|\n|prevent from|Rain prevented us from going out.|\n|suffer from|He suffers from back pain.|\n\n## vs of (재료)\n- **from**: 원형을 알 수 없음 — Wine is made from grapes.\n- **of**: 원형이 보임 — The table is made of wood.\n\n## 연습\n1. Where are you _____? (from / of)\n2. She suffers _____ migraines. (from / with)\n3. This dress is made _____ silk. (of / from) — silk이 보이니 of\n\n**정답**: 1. from  2. from  3. of"}, {"name": "28-for", "content": "# for\n\n> '~을 향해/위해' — 목적, 대상, 기간, 대가\n\n## 감각 확장\n### 목적·위함\n- I study for the test.\n- This gift is for you.\n\n### 기간\n- I've lived here for 3 years.\n- Wait for a moment.\n\n### 대가·교환\n- I paid $10 for this.\n- Thank you for your help.\n\n### 찬성·지지\n- I voted for her.\n- Are you for or against the plan?\n\n### 이유\n- Seoul is famous for its food.\n- He was fined for speeding.\n\n## 동사 조합\n| 패턴 | 예문 |\n|go for|I'll go for the steak.|\n|look for|I'm looking for my keys.|\n|wait for|Wait for me!|\n|ask for|She asked for help.|\n|make up for|He made up for his mistake.|\n|stand for|What does NASA stand for?|\n\n## vs during (기간)\n- **for**: 기간의 길이 — for 3 hours\n- **during**: 특정 이벤트 동안 — during the meeting\n\n## 연습\n1. I've been waiting _____ an hour. (for / since)\n2. What is this tool _____? (for / to)\n3. She's looking _____ a new apartment. (for / at)\n\n**정답**: 1. for  2. for  3. for"}, {"name": "29-with", "content": "# with\n\n> '나란히 함께' — 동반, 도구, 원인, 특성\n\n## 감각 확장\n### 동반\n- I went with my friend.\n- I agree with you.\n\n### 도구·수단\n- Cut it with scissors.\n- She opened it with a key.\n\n### 원인·감정\n- He was shaking with fear.\n- She cried with joy.\n\n### 특성·소유\n- A man with glasses.\n- A house with a garden.\n\n### 관계\n- What's wrong with it?\n- I'm done with this.\n\n## 동사 조합\n| 패턴 | 예문 |\n|deal with|How do you deal with stress?|\n|go with|This shirt goes with those pants.|\n|get along with|She gets along with everyone.|\n|come up with|He came up with a great idea.|\n|put up with|I can't put up with this anymore.|\n|keep up with|I can't keep up with the news.|\n\n## vs by (수단)\n- **with**: 도구 (물리적) — write with a pen\n- **by**: 방법·수단 — travel by train, pay by card\n\n## 연습\n1. She filled the cup _____ water. (with / of)\n2. I can't deal _____ this anymore. (with / about)\n3. He was trembling _____ cold. (with / from) — 둘 다 가능\n\n**정답**: 1. with  2. with  3. with/from"}, {"name": "30-without", "content": "# without\n\n> '함께 있지 않은' — with의 부정\n\n## 감각\n### 없이\n- I can't live without coffee.\n- She left without saying goodbye.\n\n### ~하지 않고\n- He solved it without any help.\n- Without thinking, she jumped in.\n\n## 핵심 패턴\n- without + 명사: without money, without doubt\n- without + -ing: without knowing, without telling me\n- go without: I can't go without sleep.\n- do without: We'll have to do without.\n\n## 함정\n- (X) without to say → (O) without saying (without + -ing)\n\n## 연습\n1. She passed the test _____ studying. (without / not)\n2. I can't do _____ my morning coffee. (without / with)\n\n**정답**: 1. without  2. without"}, {"name": "31-about", "content": "# about\n\n> 주변을 '맴도는' 감각 — 주제, 대략, ~하려는 참\n\n## 감각 확장\n### 주제: ~에 관하여\n핵심을 직접 찌르지 않고 그 주변을 도는 감각.\n- What's the movie about?\n- I'm worried about the exam.\n\n### 대략\n정확한 점이 아닌 그 근처.\n- There were about 100 people.\n- It's about 10 minutes away.\n\n### ~하려는 참\n행동의 바로 근처에 와 있는 감각.\n- I'm about to leave.\n- The train is about to depart.\n\n## 동사 조합\n| 패턴 | 예문 |\n|talk about|Let's talk about the plan.|\n|think about|I'll think about it.|\n|worry about|Don't worry about it.|\n|bring about|What brought about the change?|\n|come about|How did this come about?|\n\n## vs on (주제)\n- **about**: 일반적 주제 — talk about music\n- **on**: 학술적·공식적 — a lecture on economics\n\n## 연습\n1. What are you talking _____? (about / on)\n2. She's _____ to start her presentation. (about / around)\n3. There are _____ 50 students in the class. (about / around) — 둘 다 가능\n\n**정답**: 1. about  2. about  3. about/around"}, {"name": "32-at", "content": "# at\n\n> 정확한 한 '점'을 찍는다 — 지점, 시각, 겨냥\n\n## 감각 확장\n### 지점: 한 점\n넓은 면이 아닌 점 하나를 가리키는 감각.\n- I'm at the station.\n- She's at home. / He's at work.\n\n### 시각: 정확한 시점\n- The meeting starts at 3 o'clock.\n- I wake up at 6 every day.\n\n### 겨냥: 향해 쏘다\n시선이나 행동이 한 점을 향하는 감각.\n- Look at me.\n- She laughed at his joke.\n- Don't shout at me!\n\n### 능력·상태\n어떤 점에 위치해 있는 감각.\n- She's good at math.\n- He's bad at cooking.\n\n### 속도·가격\n- driving at 60mph\n- selling at $5 each\n\n## vs in\n- **at**: 점 (좁은 지점) — at the bus stop\n- **in**: 면·공간 (넓은 곳) — in the city\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I'm good in math. → (O) I'm good at math.\n- (X) Look at to me. → (O) Look at me.\n- (X) She arrived in the airport. → (O) She arrived at the airport.\n\n## 연습\n1. The train arrives _____ 5:30. (at / in)\n2. She's really good _____ singing. (at / in)\n3. He threw the ball _____ me. (at / to) — at은 겨냥(공격적), to는 전달\n\n**정답**: 1. at  2. at  3. at (던져 맞추다) / to (건네주다)"}, {"name": "33-by", "content": "# by\n\n> 바로 '옆을 지나' — 근접, 수단, 기한, 차이\n\n## 감각 확장\n### 옆에: 근접\n- She sat by the window.\n- The house by the lake.\n\n### 수단: ~에 의해 / ~로\n- Made by Apple. / Travel by train.\n- Pay by credit card.\n\n### 기한: ~까지\n- Finish it by Friday.\n- I'll be there by 5.\n\n### 차이\n- She won by 2 points.\n- He missed the train by 5 minutes.\n\n### 단위\n- one by one / day by day / step by step\n\n## 동사 조합\n| 패턴 | 예문 |\n|go by|Time goes by so fast.|\n|get by|We can get by on this budget.|\n|stand by|I'll stand by you no matter what.|\n|come by|Come by my office later.|\n|pass by|She passed by without noticing me.|\n\n## vs until (기한)\n- **by**: ~까지 (그 전에 완료) — Finish by Friday.\n- **until**: ~까지 (그때까지 계속) — I'll wait until Friday.\n\n## 연습\n1. The report must be done _____ Monday. (by / until)\n2. She goes to work _____ bus. (by / with)\n3. He won the race _____ a second. (by / with)\n\n**정답**: 1. by  2. by  3. by"}, {"name": "34-between", "content": "# between\n\n> 두 지점 '사이에'\n\n## 감각\n### 공간·시간: 두 개 사이\n- The bank is between the cafe and the bookstore.\n- Between 9 and 5.\n\n### 선택\n- Choose between A and B.\n- It's hard to decide between the two.\n\n### 관계: 둘 사이의 일\n- This stays between us.\n- There's a big difference between them.\n\n## vs among\n- **between**: 둘 사이 — between you and me\n- **among**: 셋 이상 무리 속 — among friends\n\n## 연습\n1. The secret is _____ you and me. (between / among)\n2. She couldn't choose _____ the two options. (between / from)\n\n**정답**: 1. between  2. between"}, {"name": "35-among", "content": "# among\n\n> 셋 이상의 무리 '속에'\n\n## 감각\n### 무리 속에\n- She sat among her friends.\n- He's popular among students.\n\n### 포함\n- Among other things, we discussed the budget.\n- She's among the best in the field.\n\n## vs between\n- **among**: 무리 속 — among the crowd\n- **between**: 둘 사이 — between two people\n\n## 연습\n1. He distributed the candy _____ the children. (among / between)\n2. _____ other issues, we talked about salary. (Among / Between)\n\n**정답**: 1. among  2. Among"}, {"name": "36-against", "content": "# against\n\n> '맞서다/맞닿다' — 반대, 접촉, 대비, 방어\n\n## 감각\n### 반대\n- I'm against the idea.\n- It's against the rules.\n\n### 맞닿음·기댐\n- She leaned against the wall.\n- The rain hit against the window.\n\n### 대비·방어\n- Save money against a rainy day.\n- Vaccinate against the flu.\n\n### 배경\n- The building stood out against the blue sky.\n\n## 연습\n1. Are you for or _____ the proposal? (against / with)\n2. She leaned _____ the door. (against / on)\n3. We need protection _____ hackers. (against / from) — 둘 다 가능\n\n**정답**: 1. against  2. against  3. against/from"}, {"name": "37-into", "content": "# into\n\n> 밖에서 '안으로 들어가는 동작' — in이 결과면 into는 과정\n\n## 감각\n### 안으로 (동작)\n- She walked into the room.\n- Pour the water into the glass.\n\n### 변화: ~으로 바뀜\n- The frog turned into a prince.\n- They broke into tears.\n\n### 충돌: 들이받음\n- He ran into a wall.\n- I bumped into an old friend. (우연히 만남)\n\n### 몰두\n- She got into music. (빠지다)\n- He's really into cooking these days.\n\n## vs in\n- **into**: 이동·변화 (동적) — walk into the room\n- **in**: 위치·상태 (정적) — be in the room\n\n## 연습\n1. She poured coffee _____ the cup. (into / in)\n2. He's really _____ photography these days. (into / in)\n3. The caterpillar turned _____ a butterfly. (into / to)\n\n**정답**: 1. into  2. into  3. into"}, {"name": "38-onto", "content": "# onto\n\n> 표면 '위로 올라가는 동작' — on이 결과면 onto는 과정\n\n## 감각\n### 위로 올라감\n- The cat jumped onto the table.\n- She climbed onto the roof.\n\n### 붙잡음\n- Hold onto the railing.\n- She held onto hope.\n\n## vs on\n- **onto**: 이동 (동적) — jump onto the stage\n- **on**: 위치 (정적) — stand on the stage\n\n## 연습\n1. The dog jumped _____ the couch. (onto / on)\n2. Hold _____ the rope tightly. (onto / on)\n\n**정답**: 1. onto  2. onto"}, {"name": "39-before", "content": "# before\n\n> '앞에' — 시간적으로 먼저, 공간적으로 앞에\n\n## 감각\n### 시간: ~전에\n- I'll finish before noon.\n- Think before you speak.\n\n### 공간: 앞에 (격식)\n- He appeared before the judge.\n\n### 우선\n- Health comes before money.\n\n## vs ago\n- **before**: 기준점 앞 — before lunch, before I left\n- **ago**: 지금부터 거슬러 — 3 years ago\n\n## 연습\n1. I need to leave _____ 5 o'clock. (before / until)\n2. She arrived _____ me. (before / ago)\n\n**정답**: 1. before  2. before"}, {"name": "40-after", "content": "# after\n\n> '뒤를 따라' — 시간 후, 추적, ~을 따서\n\n## 감각\n### 시간: ~후에\n- I'll call you after lunch.\n- After the movie, we went home.\n\n### 추적: 뒤를 쫓다\n- The police went after the thief.\n- She takes after her mother. (닮다)\n\n### 돌봄: 뒤를 챙기다\n- Who looks after the kids?\n\n### ~을 따서\n- She was named after her grandmother.\n\n## 동사 조합\n| 패턴 | 예문 |\n|look after|Look after yourself.|\n|go after|Go after your dreams.|\n|take after|He takes after his father.|\n\n## 연습\n1. I'll meet you _____ work. (after / later)\n2. She _____ after her mother in looks. (takes / goes)\n3. Who looks _____ the dog when you travel? (after / for)\n\n**정답**: 1. after  2. takes  3. after"}, {"name": "41-during", "content": "# during\n\n> 어떤 이벤트가 '진행되는 동안'\n\n## 감각\n- I fell asleep during the movie.\n- Don't use your phone during class.\n\n## vs for\n- **during**: 이벤트 동안 — during the meeting (회의라는 이벤트)\n- **for**: 기간의 길이 — for 2 hours (2시간이라는 길이)\n\n## 함정\n- (X) during 3 hours → (O) for 3 hours (숫자 기간은 for)\n- (X) during I was sleeping → (O) while I was sleeping (절이면 while)\n\n## 연습\n1. It rained _____ the night. (during / for)\n2. I studied _____ 3 hours. (for / during)\n\n**정답**: 1. during  2. for"}, {"name": "42-since", "content": "# since\n\n> '시작점부터 지금까지' — 기원과 이유\n\n## 감각\n### 시간: ~이래로\n- I've lived here since 2020.\n- She's been working since morning.\n\n### 이유: ~이므로\n- Since you asked, I'll tell you.\n- Since it's raining, let's stay home.\n\n## vs for\n- **since**: 시작 시점 — since Monday (월요일부터)\n- **for**: 기간 길이 — for 3 days (3일 동안)\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I live here since 2020. → (O) I've lived here since 2020. (현재완료 필수)\n\n## 연습\n1. She's been sick _____ last week. (since / for)\n2. _____ you're here, can you help me? (Since / For)\n\n**정답**: 1. since  2. Since"}, {"name": "43-until", "content": "# until (till)\n\n> '그 시점에 도달할 때까지' 계속\n\n## 감각\n- I'll wait until 5 o'clock.\n- Don't open it until Christmas.\n- She didn't sleep until midnight.\n\n## vs by\n- **until**: ~까지 계속 — Wait until Friday. (금요일까지 계속 기다려)\n- **by**: ~까지 완료 — Finish by Friday. (금요일 전에 끝내)\n\n## 함정\n- (X) I'll finish until Friday. → (O) I'll finish by Friday. (완료는 by)\n- until = till (till이 더 캐주얼)\n\n## 연습\n1. The store is open _____ 10 p.m. (until / by)\n2. I need to submit this _____ tomorrow. (by / until)\n\n**정답**: 1. until  2. by"}, {"name": "44-within", "content": "# within\n\n> 경계를 넘지 않는 '안쪽'\n\n## 감각\n### 시간: ~이내\n- I'll be there within an hour.\n- Please reply within 3 days.\n\n### 범위: 안쪽\n- The target is within reach.\n- Keep it within budget.\n\n### 내면\n- The answer lies within yourself.\n\n## vs in\n- **within**: 경계를 강조 (넘지 않는다) — within 24 hours\n- **in**: 단순 안 — in 24 hours (24시간 후)\n\n## 연습\n1. We must finish _____ the deadline. (within / until)\n2. The hotel is _____ walking distance. (within / in)\n\n**정답**: 1. within  2. within"}, {"name": "45-of", "content": "# of\n\n> '~로부터 나온/~에 속한' — 영어에서 가장 빈도 높은 전치사\n\n## 감각\n### 소속·부분\n- A cup of coffee.\n- The roof of the building.\n- One of my friends.\n\n### 관련·대상\n- I'm afraid of spiders.\n- She's proud of her son.\n- Think of a number.\n\n### 분리·박탈\n- He robbed me of my wallet.\n- The city was emptied of people.\n\n### 원인\n- He died of cancer.\n\n### 특성\n- A man of courage.\n- A woman of great talent.\n\n### 재료 (원형 보임)\n- A table made of wood.\n\n## 함정\n- (X) a cup of a coffee → (O) a cup of coffee\n- (X) I'm afraid from spiders. → (O) I'm afraid of spiders.\n- (X) He died from cancer. → (O) He died of cancer. (질병 원인은 of)\n\n## 연습\n1. She's one _____ the best singers. (of / in)\n2. A glass _____ water, please. (of / with)\n3. I'm thinking _____ you. (of / about) — 둘 다 가능\n\n**정답**: 1. of  2. of  3. of/about"}, {"name": "46-as", "content": "# as\n\n> '같은 자격으로' — 역할, 비교, 이유, 동시\n\n## 감각\n### 역할: ~로서\n- She works as a nurse.\n- He acted as a translator.\n\n### 비교: ~처럼\n- As usual, he was late.\n- Do as I say.\n\n### 이유: ~이므로\n- As it was raining, we stayed home.\n\n### 동시: ~하면서\n- As I walked in, everyone looked at me.\n\n### 비교 구문\n- as tall as, as soon as, as far as\n\n## vs like\n- **as**: 실제 역할/자격 — She works as a teacher. (선생님으로)\n- **like**: 닮음/유사 — She acts like a teacher. (선생님처럼)\n\n## 연습\n1. She started her career _____ an intern. (as / like)\n2. _____ I said before, we need more time. (As / Like)\n3. He's not _____ tall _____ his brother. (as...as / so...like)\n\n**정답**: 1. as  2. As  3. as...as"}, {"name": "47-like", "content": "# like\n\n> '닮은' — ~처럼, ~같은\n\n## 감각\n### ~처럼\n- She looks like her mother.\n- It feels like summer.\n- What's it like living abroad?\n\n### ~같은\n- Something like that.\n- I want a car like yours.\n\n### ~하고 싶은 (feel like)\n- I feel like eating pizza.\n- I don't feel like going out.\n\n## vs as\n- **like**: 닮음 (뒤에 명사) — She sings like a pro.\n- **as**: 자격 (뒤에 절 가능) — She sings as a pro does.\n\n## 함정\n- (X) Like I said... → 구어에서 많이 쓰지만, 문법적으로 As I said...가 정확\n\n## 연습\n1. What does it taste _____? (like / as)\n2. I feel _____ staying home today. (like / as)\n\n**정답**: 1. like  2. like"}, {"name": "48-than", "content": "# than\n\n> 비교의 '기준점'\n\n## 감각\n### 비교\n- She's taller than me.\n- This is more expensive than I thought.\n- I'd rather stay home than go out.\n\n### other than: ~외에\n- I have no choice other than to accept.\n\n### more than / less than\n- More than 100 people came.\n- It costs less than $10.\n\n## 함정\n- (X) She's taller then me. → (O) She's taller than me. (then은 \"그 다음에\")\n- (X) I prefer coffee than tea. → (O) I prefer coffee to tea. (prefer는 to)\n\n## 연습\n1. He runs faster _____ anyone else. (than / then)\n2. I'd rather walk _____ drive. (than / to)\n\n**정답**: 1. than  2. than"}, {"name": "49-beyond", "content": "# beyond\n\n> 저 '너머로' — over보다 더 먼 감각\n\n## 감각\n### 공간: 넘어서\n- The village is just beyond the hill.\n\n### 초과: 범위 밖\n- It's beyond my understanding.\n- This is beyond repair.\n- She's beautiful beyond words.\n\n## 연습\n1. The answer is _____ my knowledge. (beyond / over)\n2. The park is just _____ the bridge. (beyond / across)\n\n**정답**: 1. beyond  2. beyond"}, {"name": "50-toward", "content": "# toward(s)\n\n> '~쪽으로' — to보다 부드러운 방향, 도달이 아닌 지향\n\n## 감각\n### 방향\n- She walked toward the door.\n- The car is heading toward us.\n\n### 태도\n- What's your attitude toward this?\n\n### 목적\n- We're working toward a solution.\n- Save toward your retirement.\n\n## vs to\n- **toward**: 방향만 (도착 X) — walking toward the station\n- **to**: 도착 포함 — walking to the station\n\n## 연습\n1. She has a positive attitude _____ life. (toward / for)\n2. He walked slowly _____ the exit. (toward / to) — 둘 다 가능\n\n**정답**: 1. toward  2. toward/to"}, {"name": "51-beside", "content": "# beside / besides\n\n> beside: '옆에' / besides: '게다가'\n\n## 감각\n### beside: 옆에 (위치)\n- She sat beside me.\n- The park is right beside the school.\n\n### besides: 게다가 / ~외에 (추가)\n- Besides English, she speaks French.\n- I'm tired. Besides, it's too late.\n\n## 함정\n- beside와 besides를 혼동하지 말 것\n- beside = next to (위치)\n- besides = in addition to (추가)\n\n## 연습\n1. Who was sitting _____ you? (beside / besides)\n2. _____ the cost, there are other problems. (Besides / Beside)\n\n**정답**: 1. beside  2. Besides"}, {"name": "52-under-below-beneath", "content": "# under / below / beneath\n\n> 모두 '아래'지만 뉘앙스가 다르다\n\n## 감각 차이\n### under: 바로 아래 (가장 일반적)\n직접 덮여 있는 감각.\n- The cat is under the table.\n- She's under a lot of pressure.\n- children under 12\n\n### below: 기준선 아래\n수치·위치가 어떤 기준보다 낮은 감각.\n- below average / below zero\n- The apartment below us is noisy.\n\n### beneath: 격식·추상 (아래 + 격에 미치지 못함)\n- beneath the surface (표면 아래)\n- This task is beneath him. (그의 격에 안 맞는)\n\n## 정리\n| | 감각 | 예문 |\n|under|직접 아래·덮임|under the bridge|\n|below|기준 이하|below sea level|\n|beneath|격식·추상 아래|beneath his dignity|\n\n## 연습\n1. The temperature dropped _____ zero. (below / under)\n2. The dog hid _____ the bed. (under / below)\n3. Such behavior is _____ her. (beneath / under)\n\n**정답**: 1. below  2. under  3. beneath"}, {"name": "53-above", "content": "# above\n\n> 접촉 없이 '위에' — over와 달리 넘어가지 않는다\n\n## 감각\n### 위에 (접촉 없이)\n- The clouds are above us.\n- The apartment above mine is noisy.\n\n### 기준 초과\n- above average\n- above 30 degrees\n\n### 격·수준\n- He's above suspicion.\n- She's above that kind of behavior.\n\n## vs over\n- **above**: 정적, 접촉 없이 위에 — above the clouds\n- **over**: 동적, 넘어가는 — jump over the fence\n\n## 연습\n1. The temperature is _____ normal today. (above / over) — 둘 다 가능\n2. A bird flew _____ the house. (over / above) — 둘 다 가능, over가 더 자연스러움\n\n**정답**: 1. above/over  2. over"}, {"name": "54-throughout", "content": "# throughout\n\n> 처음부터 끝까지 '빠짐없이' — through + out\n\n## 감각\n### 기간 전체\n- It rained throughout the day.\n- She smiled throughout the interview.\n\n### 공간 전체\n- The disease spread throughout the country.\n- Music could be heard throughout the building.\n\n## vs during\n- **throughout**: 처음부터 끝까지 전부 — throughout the year\n- **during**: 그 기간 중 어느 시점 — during the year\n\n## 연습\n1. He traveled _____ Asia last summer. (throughout / through)\n2. It snowed _____ the night. (throughout / during) — 둘 다 가능, throughout이 \"밤새 내내\"\n\n**정답**: 1. throughout  2. throughout"}, {"name": "55-despite", "content": "# despite (in spite of)\n\n> '~에도 불구하고' — 양보\n\n## 감각\n예상과 반대되는 결과. 장애물이 있지만 결과는 달랐다.\n- Despite the rain, we had a great time.\n- She passed the exam despite being sick.\n- In spite of the traffic, we arrived on time.\n\n## despite vs although\n- **despite** + 명사/-ing: Despite the cold, ...\n- **although** + 절: Although it was cold, ...\n\n## 함정\n- (X) Despite of the rain → (O) Despite the rain (of 불필요)\n- (X) Despite it rained → (O) Despite the rain / Although it rained\n\n## 연습\n1. _____ his age, he runs every morning. (Despite / Although)\n2. She succeeded _____ all the difficulties. (despite / although)\n\n**정답**: 1. Despite  2. despite"}, {"name": "56-except", "content": "# except\n\n> '~을 제외하고' — 배제\n\n## 감각\n전체에서 하나를 빼는 감각.\n- Everyone came except Tom.\n- I like all fruit except bananas.\n- The store is open every day except Sunday.\n\n## except vs besides\n- **except**: 제외 — Everyone except me. (나만 빼고)\n- **besides**: 추가 — Besides me, she invited Tom. (나 외에 Tom도)\n\n## except vs except for\n- **except**: 주어 뒤 직접 — Everyone except Tom.\n- **except for**: 문장 앞·중간 — Except for the ending, the movie was great.\n\n## 함정\n- (X) except of → (O) except / except for\n\n## 연습\n1. I eat everything _____ seafood. (except / besides)\n2. _____ the noise, the hotel was perfect. (Except for / Except)\n\n**정답**: 1. except  2. Except for"}];